 leadership skills. Superior writing and editing skills with the ability to construct well-founded, clear, and concise analyses and recommendations. Strong attention to detail. Ability to lead and manage day to day aspects of engagement activities and an ability to work with clients Strong analytical skills. Ability to handle complex information, solve problems, and manage multiple tasks. Ability to communicate effectively with clients and within all levels of the organization. Ability to establish and maintain positive relationships and build teams. Strong reputation for integrity and ethics. PromRoW Required Technical and Professional Expertise Required Professional and Technical Expertise Undergraduate degree is required. At least 8 years of experience banking, financial services industry or government regulatory agency. Technical expertise and experience in compliance, risk management, corporate governance, accounting, or legal or regulatory issues, finance, lending, trading and/or other financial services core competencies. Demonstrated experience in building and managing project teams to address complex issues in high pressure situations. Track record working in an unstructured environment where engagement leaders are expected to identify and develop innovative solutions to client challenge Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise Preferred Professional and Technical Expertise Graduate degree MBA, PhD, JD. About Business Unit IBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence. Your Life @ IBM What m